  <h2 id="framing">2. Framing — $3,200–4,500</h2>
  <p>2&times;4 walls with exterior continuous insulation. Maximizes interior width (113") and saves weight vs 2&times;6.</p>
  <div class="table-wrap">
    <table>
      <thead><tr><th>Item</th><th>Cost</th></tr></thead>
      <tbody>
        <tr><td>Wall studs, plates, headers (~200 studs + plates)</td><td>$800–1,000</td></tr>
        <tr><td>Roof rafters (2&times;6 or 2&times;8, ~15 rafters + ridge)</td><td>$400–600</td></tr>
        <tr><td>Loft floor joists (2&times;8 or 2&times;10, 8' span)</td><td>$200–300</td></tr>
        <tr><td>Subfloor sheathing (3/4" T&amp;G plywood, ~260 sq ft)</td><td>$500–700</td></tr>
        <tr><td>Wall sheathing (1/2" plywood or OSB, ~720 sq ft)</td><td>$600–900</td></tr>
        <tr><td>Roof sheathing (1/2" plywood, ~286 sq ft)</td><td>$300–400</td></tr>
        <tr><td>Misc blocking, nailers, trim lumber</td><td>$200–300</td></tr>
        <tr><td>Fasteners, hardware, hangers, straps</td><td>$200–300</td></tr>
      </tbody>
    </table>
  </div>

  <h2 id="insulation">3. Insulation &amp; Air Sealing</h2>
  <p>2&times;4 cavity: <a href="https://www.rockwool.com/north-america/products-and-applications/products/comfortbatt/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Rockwool R-15</a>. Two options for exterior continuous insulation — both vapor-open, both R-6+, same total wall performance.</p>

  <h3>Option A: Gutex wood fiber — $5,010–5,110</h3>
  <p>Premium. <a href="https://gutex.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Gutex</a>/<a href="https://www.steico.com/en" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Steico</a> wood fiber board acts as insulation + WRB in one layer (taped seams). No separate house wrap needed. Lowest embodied carbon. Specialty order from <a href="https://475.supply/products/gutex-multitherm" target="_blank" rel="noopener">475 Supply</a>.</p>
  <div class="table-wrap">
    <table>
      <thead><tr><th>Item</th><th>Qty</th><th>$/sf</th><th>Cost</th></tr></thead>
      <tbody>
        <tr><td>Rockwool ComfortBatt R-15 (walls)</td><td>~720 sf</td><td>$1.40</td><td>$1,010</td></tr>
        <tr><td>Rockwool ComfortBatt R-15 (floor)</td><td>~260 sf</td><td>$1.40</td><td>$365</td></tr>
        <tr><td>Rockwool R-30 or dense-pack cellulose (roof)</td><td>~286 sf</td><td>$1.80</td><td>$515</td></tr>
        <tr><td>Gutex/Steico wood fiber board 1.5" (exterior)</td><td>~720 sf</td><td>$3.50</td><td>$2,520</td></tr>
        <tr><td>Intello Plus smart vapor retarder</td><td>~900 sf</td><td>$0.50</td><td>$450</td></tr>
        <tr><td>Air sealing tapes (Tescon, Uni Tape)</td><td>—</td><td>—</td><td>$150–250</td></tr>
      </tbody>
    </table>
  </div>

  <h3>Option B: Rockwool Comfortboard 80 — $4,170–4,270</h3>
  <p>Budget. <a href="https://www.rockwool.com/north-america/products-and-applications/products/comfortboard-80/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Comfortboard 80</a> is rigid mineral wool — same R-value (R-6.3), vapor-open, noncombustible. Available at Lowe's/HD. Needs separate house wrap since it's not a WRB.</p>
  <div class="table-wrap">
    <table>
      <thead><tr><th>Item</th><th>Qty</th><th>$/sf</th><th>Cost</th></tr></thead>
      <tbody>
        <tr><td>Rockwool ComfortBatt R-15 (walls)</td><td>~720 sf</td><td>$1.40</td><td>$1,010</td></tr>
        <tr><td>Rockwool ComfortBatt R-15 (floor)</td><td>~260 sf</td><td>$1.40</td><td>$365</td></tr>
        <tr><td>Rockwool R-30 or dense-pack cellulose (roof)</td><td>~286 sf</td><td>$1.80</td><td>$515</td></tr>
        <tr><td>Rockwool Comfortboard 80 1.5" (exterior)</td><td>~720 sf</td><td>$2.18</td><td>$1,570</td></tr>
        <tr><td>House wrap (Tyvek or similar, over plywood)</td><td>~720 sf</td><td>$0.15</td><td>$110</td></tr>
        <tr><td>Intello Plus smart vapor retarder</td><td>~900 sf</td><td>$0.50</td><td>$450</td></tr>
        <tr><td>Air sealing tapes (Tescon, Uni Tape)</td><td>—</td><td>—</td><td>$150–250</td></tr>
      </tbody>
    </table>
  </div>
  <div class="note">
    <p><strong>Savings:</strong> Option B saves ~$840 vs Option A with equivalent thermal performance (R-21 total wall, no bridging). Both are vapor-open and work with the Intello Plus interior. Option A is the "one product does two jobs" premium play; Option B is more conventional and readily available.</p>
  </div>

